  <T n="name">0xB20EBC68<!--String: "Holidays"--></T>
  <U n="notification">
    <L n="ui_responses">
      <U>
        <T n="text">0xA13F0B8C<!--String: "Learn More   NOT USED"--></T>
        <E n="ui_request">SHOW_LESSONS</E>
      </U>
    </L>
  </U>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b226</T>
      <T n="text">0x77F0A275<!--String: "Holidays are special days where Sims can celebrate their favorite Traditions. There are unique Holidays already on the Calendar but you can also create your own Holidays.  Holidays are marked on the Calendar with a large icon."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b225</T>
      <T n="text">0xE48C275E<!--String: "Each Holiday can have up to five Traditions. A tradition is something Sims like to do as part of their holiday, but some Sims may ignore them, depending on their age or traits."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b224</T>
      <T n="text">0x7CAF8766<!--String: "When the Holiday starts, each Sim will show the Traditions they care about; some Sims will LOVE a particular Tradition.  For example, children love to open presents as their tradition! Traditions that Sims love will have a heart behind it."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b223</T>
      <T n="text">0xA393ACD4<!--String: "Hover over the tradition to see how Sims can satisfy them. Each time they fulfill a tradition, they will earn more Satisfaction Points when the Holiday is complete!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b222</T>
      <T n="text">0xA4B0891D<!--String: "Some traditions take more than one thing to complete. If you've only made progress on the tradition but haven't completed it, you'll be alerted by a flashing checkmark."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\Holidays_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:ee8e85930139b221</T>
      <T n="text">0xC66D391E<!--String: "Creating your own Holiday is as simple as opening the Calendar and picking a day that doesn’t already have a Holiday. Select Add Holiday, but just make sure it’s not on the day you’re currently on!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
